Definition: poisoning by ingestion of ergot-infected grain products
Example: characterized by thirst and diarrhea and nausea and cramping and vomiting and abnormal cardiac rhythms; in severe cases it can cause seizures and gangrene of the limbs
Synonyms: poisoning, by, ingestion, of, ergot-infected, grain, products, characterized, thirst, and, diarrhea, nausea, cramping, vomiting, abnormal, cardiac, rhythms, in, severe, cases, it, can, cause, seizures, gangrene, the, limbs
Category: noun.state
